## Enhanced Error Handling Patterns

### Robust Pattern with Retry Logic
```bash
cd ~ && nix-shell -p nodejs expect --run 'expect -c "
set timeout 30
set max_retries 3
set retry_count 0

proc handle_error {msg} {
  global retry_count max_retries
  send_user \"\\nError: \$msg\\n\"
  incr retry_count
  if {\$retry_count < \$max_retries} {
    send_user \"Retrying (\$retry_count/\$max_retries)...\\n\"
    return 1
  }
  return 0
}

spawn npx @anthropic-ai/claude-code --dangerously-skip-permissions \"[TASK]\"

expect {
  -re {.*bypass permissions.*} {
    send \"2\r\"
    exp_continue
  }
  -re {.*Write.*|.*created.*|.*saved.*} {
    send_user \"\\nSuccess detected\\n\"
    exit 0
  }
  -re {Connection refused|Connection reset} {
    if {[handle_error \"Connection lost\"]} {
      spawn npx @anthropic-ai/claude-code --dangerously-skip-permissions \"[TASK]\"
      exp_continue
    }
    exit 1
  }
  eof {
    if {[handle_error \"Unexpected EOF\"]} {
      spawn npx @anthropic-ai/claude-code --dangerously-skip-permissions \"[TASK]\"
      exp_continue
    }
    exit 1
  }
  timeout {
    send_user \"\\nTimeout after \$timeout seconds\\n\"
    exit 124
  }
}
"'
```

### Error Detection with Exit Codes
```bash
cd ~ && nix-shell -p nodejs expect --run 'expect -c "
set timeout 30
set exit_code 0

spawn npx @anthropic-ai/claude-code --dangerously-skip-permissions \"[TASK]\"

expect {
  -re {.*bypass permissions.*} {
    send \"2\r\"
    exp_continue
  }
  -re {ERROR:|FATAL:|Failed|Exception} {
    send_user \"\\nError detected in output\\n\"
    set exit_code 1
    exp_continue
  }
  -re {.*Write.*|.*completed.*} {
    exit \$exit_code
  }
  timeout {
    exit 124  # Standard timeout exit code
  }
}
"' && echo \"Success\" || echo \"Failed with code: $?\"
```

### Connection Recovery Pattern
```bash
cd ~ && nix-shell -p nodejs expect --run 'expect -c "
set timeout 30
set connection_attempts 0

while {\$connection_attempts < 3} {
  incr connection_attempts
  spawn npx @anthropic-ai/claude-code --dangerously-skip-permissions \"[TASK]\"

  expect {
    -re {.*bypass permissions.*} {
      send \"2\r\"
      exp_continue
    }
    -re {.*Write.*|.*saved.*} {
      send_user \"\\nTask completed successfully\\n\"
      exit 0
    }
    eof {
      send_user \"\\nConnection lost, attempt \$connection_attempts/3\\n\"
      if {\$connection_attempts >= 3} {
        exit 1
      }
      sleep 2
    }
    timeout {
      send_user \"\\nTimeout on attempt \$connection_attempts\\n\"
      if {\$connection_attempts >= 3} {
        exit 124
      }
    }
  }
}
"'
```

## Troubleshooting Guide

### Common Issues and Solutions

| Issue | Cause | Solution | Exit Code |
|-------|-------|----------|-----------|
| "Raw mode not supported" | Direct piping to Claude Code | Use expect for TTY emulation | 1 |
| "No shell.nix found" | Wrong directory | Always `cd ~` first | 1 |
| Hangs indefinitely | Pattern not matching | Check output, adjust regex | 124 |
| Immediate exit | Success pattern too broad | Make patterns more specific | 0 |
| Permission denied | Missing --dangerously-skip-permissions | Add the flag | 126 |
| Connection refused | Network/service issue | Use retry logic | 111 |
| Authentication failed | Wrong credentials | Check password | 2 |
| Unexpected EOF | Process crash | Implement recovery | 1 |

